<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-23-0987 </DOCNO><TEXT>An overview is given of the 17th World Gas conference, held in WashingtonD.C., june 1988. The discussions on the significance of gas as an energycarrier are highlighted. The items are the International Gas Union; thecongress; the Russian gas industry; Norwegian's place in the gas market;the importance of gas for Europe; the changes in the gas market; theprivatization of British Gas; cooperation in research and developmentand the agressive research and development programs in Japan. 22 figs.</TEXT></DOC>